messages.reasoning_content:
Interesting! Lines 8642-8663 already have a very relevant pattern! It handles exactly the case we need:

```
// fcmp o{eq|gt|ge|lt|le|ne} (select (fcmp ord %x, 0.0), %x, 0.0), C
//   --> fcmp o{eq|gt|ge|lt|le|ne} %x, C
// fcmp o{eq|gt|ge|lt|le|ne} (select (fcmp uno %x, 0.0), 0.0, %x), C
//   --> fcmp o{eq|gt|ge|lt|le|ne} %x, C
// This is valid when fcmp P 0.0, C is false (same as fcmp P NaN, C = false
// for ordered predicates), so replacing NaN with 0.0 doesn't change the result.
```

This already handles the case! Let me check if it's triggered. The condition is:
1. `FCmpInst::isOrdered(Pred)` - `oeq` is ordered, so yes
2. The select matches `m_Select(m_SpecificFCmp(FCmpInst::FCMP_ORD, ...), m_Specific(X), m_AnyZeroFP())`
